2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes an efficient implementation of dynamic objects, which is a core topic in data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.Distributed - The paper deals with the problem of implementing dynamic objects in a distributed setting, which falls under the scope of distributed computing. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper presents a system for implementing dynamic objects, which can be considered as a control problem. 
5. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper proposes a universal construction for implementing dynamic objects, which can be of interest to programming language researchers.
